ğŸ” Java Program to Find Character Occurrence in a String

Exploring one of the fundamental yet essential concepts in Java: counting the number of times each character appears in a string.

ğŸ’¡ Hereâ€™s a Java snippet that prints the frequency of characters in a string:



import java.util.HashMap;

import java.util.Map;


public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        String input = "hello";

        char[] arr = input.toCharArray();

        Map<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();



        for (char ch : arr) {

            int count = 1;

            if (map.containsKey(ch)) {

                count = map.get(ch) + 1;

            }

            map.put(ch, count);

        }



        System.out.println(map);

    }

}



âœ… What this code does:

Converts the input string into a character array.

Uses a HashMap to store character frequencies.

Updates the count each time a character appears again.



ğŸ§  Output for "hello":

{h=1, e=1, l=2, o=1}



